body:
Date: {{date}}

To: Assigned Vocational Rehabilitation Counselor (VRC)
VA Regional Office

Subject: Request for Serious Employment Handicap (SEH) Determination (38 C.F.R. § 21.52)
Veteran: {{userName}}
VA Claim Number: {{claimNumber}}

Dear Counselor,

I am writing to formally request a determination that I have a Serious Employment Handicap (SEH) under 38 C.F.R. § 21.52.

This determination is necessary because:
- My disability rating is 10% (requiring an SEH to establish entitlement), or
- I require an extension of my 12-year basic period of eligibility under 38 C.F.R. § 21.44, or
- I require an extension of my training services beyond 48 months under 38 C.F.R. § 21.78.

Under 38 C.F.R. § 21.52, an SEH exists when a veteran has a significant impairment of their ability to prepare for, obtain, or retain employment consistent with their abilities, aptitudes, and interests, caused in substantial part by the contribution of service-connected disabilities.

My service-connected conditions impose severe limitations on my employability due to the following factors:
{{employmentBarriers}}

Specific Serious Employment Handicap indicators present in my case include:
{{sehJustification}}

I request that a formal evaluation be conducted and that an SEH be approved to support my rehabilitation plan.

Sincerely,

{{userName}}
